The remains of two Air Force fliers missing in Southeast Asia for three decades have been identified and returned to their families for burial , the Pentagon has announced .
To the Editor : Re `` The Unknown Soldier May Be Known '' ( editorial , Feb. 21 ) : You mention some 2,000 American troops missing in action in Vietnam still unaccounted for .
PRESIDING over the ceremony adding the remains of a soldier killed in Vietnam to the Tomb of the Unknowns in 1984 , President Reagan vowed that the nation would never abandon its efforts to account for all those still missing from that divisive war .
Vietnam said today that it is releasing 5,219 prisoners , including an unspecified number of American expatriates , as part of a general amnesty .